Executive Profile
Bruce H. Besanko  CFO & Principal Accounting Officer, Kohl's CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 6 different industries.58--
Background

		Mr. Bruce H. Besanko has been Chief Financial Officer and Principal Accounting Officer at Kohl's Corporation since July 10, 2017. Mr. Besanko has been Chief Financial Officer and Vice President at Unified Grocers, Inc. since June 23, 2017. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Chief Operating Officer of SUPERVALU Inc. from April 18, 2016 and October 1, 2015 to July 5, 2017 and served as its Executive Vice President from August 2013 to July 5, 2017. Mr. Besanko ... served as the Chief Financial Officer of SUPERVALU Inc. from August 7, 2013 to October 2015. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Finance at OfficeMax Incorporated from February 16, 2009 to August 6, 2013 and served as its Chief Administrative Officer from October 2009 to August 6, 2013. He served as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President and Vice President of Finance at Circuit City Stores Inc., from July 30, 2007 to February 15, 2009. He served as Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of Finance at Yankee Holding Corp. (formerly, Yankee Candle Co. Inc.) from April 2005 to July 30, 2007 and served as its Principal Accounting Officer until July 30, 2007. He served as Vice President of Finance and Planning & Performance Management at Best Buy Co. Inc. from April 2002 to March 17, 2005. He has a strong background in business and financial leadership. Prior to joining Best Buy in 2002, he held several financial leadership positions of increasing responsibility for Sears, Roebuck and Co. from 1996 to 2002. Prior to joining Sears, he held various Finance, Accounting and Treasury positions with the Atlantic Richfield Company from 1992 to 1996. He also served in the U.S. Air Force for 26 years, where he rose to the rank of lieutenant colonel. Mr. Besanko holds a Master of Business Administration degree in Finance and Strategy from the University of Chicago and a Bachelor of Science degree in Psychology from the University of Cincinnati.Read Full 